      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a mechanically sound example of the iconic rear-engine platform. Powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six, this unit delivers linear power through a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle. The chassis remains taut, benefiting from a multi-link rear suspension setup and communicative hydraulic steering. Maintenance is current, including a proactive IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced water pump to ensure optimal thermal efficiency. While showing minor cosmetic patina consistent with its age, the drivetrain is robust, featuring healthy clutch engagement and no signs of bore scoring. A driver-focused machine engineered for precision.",
